CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 21, 1963, pg. 3 reads: "Survived Crash - Alidis Jones (center) of 608 Regis Way, East Liberty, whose car was hit head on by the station wagon which brought a fiery death to three men, together ...(left to right) Benjamin Norris and Frederick Barker, passengers in Jones' car, are shown shortly after telling Sarah Fields and Martha Jane Walker (right) of the accident. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of car accident survivors, from left: Benjamin Norris, Alidis Jones, and Frederick Barker, seated with  Sarah Fields and Martha Jane Walker, seated in living room interior with coffee table, two sofas, lamp, and window with blinds and floral curtains, 608 Regis Way
